1. Project Title 
File-Driven Data Processing Application using External Modules in Python 
 
2. Problem Statement 
To design and implement a file-driven application that reads data from a file, processes it using external modules, and generates useful output. The system should demonstrate modular programming and file handling techniques. 
 
3. Objective 
 
• To understand file handling in Python 
• To use external modules for modular programming • To process and analyze data from files • To improve code reusability and organization 
• To handle real-world data efficiently 
 
 
4. Tools Used 
 
•	Python 3 
 
•	VS Code / IDLE 
 
•	External Modules (custom Python files) 
 
 
5. Description 
 
This project implements a File-Driven Data Processing Application using Python. The system reads data from a file (e.g., student marks or sales data), processes it using functions defined in external modules, and displays results such as totals, averages, or filtered data. 
 
The use of external modules improves code organization and reusability. 
6. Algorithm 
 
•	Start the program 
 
•	Read data from file 
 
•	Import external module 
 
•	Process data (calculate total, average) 
 
•	Display results 
 
•	End program 
